ite, J.C., Coops, N.C., Hobart, G.W., Zaid, H.S.J., 2018b. Large-area mapping of Canadian boreal forest cover, height, biomass and other structural attributes using Landsat composites and lidar plots. Remote Sens. Environ. 209, 90-106. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.rse.2017.12.020.\nNatural Resource Canada, 2020. The State of Canada's Forests. Annual Report 2020.\nNguyen, T.H., Jones, S.D., Soto-Berolov, M., Haywood, A., Hislop, S., 2020. Monitoring aboveground forest biomass dynamics over three decades using Landsat time-series and single-date inventory data. Int. J. Appl. Earth Obs. Geolzf. 84, 101952.https:// doi.org/10.1016/j.jag.2019.101952.\nOlofsson, P., Ar√©valo, P., Espejo, A.B., Green, C., Lindquist, E., McRoberts, R.E., Sanz, M. J., 2020. Mitigating the effects of omission errors on area and area change estimates. Remote Sens. Environ. 236, 111492.https://doi.org/10.1016/j.rse.2019.111492.\nPfuit, D., Simwanda, M., Salekin, S., Nyivenda, C., Murayama, Y., Rausgalage, M., 2020. Sentinel-2 data for land cover/ran mapping: a review. Remote Sens. 12, 2291. https://doi.org/10.3390/rn12142291.\nPoliti, S., Breidenbach, J., Schumacher, J., Hauglin, M., Klingenberg, T.F., Astrup, R., 2021. Above-ground biomass change estimation using national forest inventory data with Sentinel-2 and Landsat. Remote Sens. Environ. 265, 112644.https://doi.org/ 10.1016/j.rse.2021.112644.\n\nSchroeder, T.A., Widder, M.A., Healey, S.P., Moisen, G.G., 2011. Mapping wildfire and clearcut harvest disturbances in boreal forests with Landsat time series data. Remote Sens. Environ. 115, 1421-1433. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.rse.2011.01.022.\nShang, R., Zhu, Z., Zhang, J., Qiu, S., Yang, Z., Li, T., Yang, X., 2022. Near-real-time monitoring of land disturbance with harmonized Landsat 7-8 and Sentinel-2 data. Remote Sens. Environ. 278, 113073.https://doi.org/10.1016/j.rse.2022.113073.\nShao, Z., Cai, J., Fu, P., Hu, L., Liu, T., 2019. Deep learning-based fusion of Landsat-8 and Sentinel-2 images 